---
import { site } from "@config/site";
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout meta={{ title: "About" }}>
  <article class="about prose">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      Hey there. I'm Chris, just a rookie game developer trying to build up some interesting stuff.
    </p>

    <p>
      Right now, I'm mainly learning network infrastructure, Linux, and systems programming with C
      and C++.
    </p>

    <h2>What I'm learning</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Linux networking: sockets, epoll, io_uring, XDP, and eBPF</li>
      <li>High-performance networking: RDMA, DPDK, and SPDK</li>
      <li>AI infrastructure and distributed systems</li>
      <li>Systems programming with C, C++, and a little Rust</li>
      <li>Performance analysis and optimization</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>About this blog</h2>
    <p>
      This blog is basically my public notebook. I use it to document things I'm learning,
      experiments I've tried, bugs I've run into, and ideas I still don't fully understand.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm not an expert, and I probably get things wrong sometimes. The goal is simply to keep
      pushing forward through hand coding and debugging, go a little deeper each time, and hopefully
      make some of the confusing stuff easier to understand.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Feel free to reach out on
      <a href={site.githubUrl} rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>. I'm always happy to talk about
      Linux, networking, C/C++, or anything related to systems and infrastructure.
    </p>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
  }
</style>
